What are your suggestions for creating notebooks which will need to be updated regularly, for

00:49:31.860 --> 00:49:39.860
instance, downloading uploaded data? So, like I said, the notebook is just a static HTML

00:49:39.860 --> 00:49:47.379
file. However, one thing that you may not be aware of is that it is actually possible

00:49:47.379 --> 00:49:56.219
to render one of these things, not just using that preview click inside RStudio, you could

00:49:56.219 --> 00:50:05.219
actually do it from the R console via R Markdown Render. So, you can do R Markdown Render,

00:50:05.219 --> 00:50:11.379
and you can give it the path to your notebook file, and it will render the notebook just

00:50:11.379 --> 00:50:15.659
as though you'd rendered it inside the RStudio IDE. So, you don't really need to use RStudio

00:50:15.699 --> 00:50:21.620
to render one of these things. So, if you want to actually have a notebook that updates

